<br>
Loved the books, thought the movies sucked.  Imo the storyline changes, lame characterizations and ridiculous battle scenes made the movies inane.<br>
<br>
The whole greatness of the Tolkien books was the breadth and depth of the history of Middle Earth he created, the towering heroic figures, and the titanic struggle taking place simply to distract Sauron from his true peril, while Frodo and Sam struggle on a hopeless errand to destroy the ring.  It is pretty pointless to try to recreate all that in 3 movies, even 3 very long movies.<br>
<br>
Similar to Dune, there's just too much to cover.  When you chop it down and rearrange it to fit a movie, it just turns it into a crappy story.<br>
<br>
The true test of a movie based on a book is, would you like it if the books never existed?  For myself, I doubt it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isil001>Isil001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(12/29/03 6:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2446.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Hows life been treating ya Eddie? Good I hope.<br>
